  "prompt": "Will the Indian customs department charge customs tax for a Rs90,000 DSLR camera bought in the USA?",
  "response": "Yes, the Indian customs department will likely charge customs duty on a DSLR camera purchased for Rs90,000 in the USA when it is brought into India. The specific amount of customs duty will depend on the latest regulations and the type of goods being imported. It is advisable to check with the Central Board of Indirect Taxes and Customs (CBIC) for the most current duty rates and applicable charges.\n\nTypically, items like cameras may attract customs duty, integrated GST (IGST), and other possible surcharges. Be prepared with relevant documentation and receipts to ensure a smooth customs clearance process.",
